content: South Korea's Shouyi Qingyunshan Park is relatively small in scale
It is a very spectacular spot for sunrise viewing.
The environment of the park is very good, the air is fresh and the traffic is very convenient.

The previous day, I visited the shallow mountains of Baiyun Temple in Pinggu. I accidentally stepped foot in several caves. The mouths of the caves were covered by firewood, weeds, animal waste, and construction waste. Only birds and beasts were patronized. The cave is dedicated to the painting Guanyin, good fortune, dragon girl and all the Bodhisattvas, I don't know what the age and what the person did. The guarded bhikuni did not dare to enter the hole, and it was not clear how to go. It was a long time ago.
